Show HN: PrankGPT – call your friends with GPT-3
text:
PrankGPT calls a phone number and makes GPT-3 have a back-and-forth conversation with the call recipient. Use it to prank your friends!

Demo: https://www.loom.com/share/0d0d68f1a62f409eb5ae24521293d2dc

Stack:

- GCP for both Text-to-Speech and Speech-to-Text

- Twilio for the telephony

- GPT-3 davinci-003 model (no fine-tuning) from OpenAI (where most of the latency of the response comes from)

Would love to hear any thoughts about this stack if anyone is working or has worked on something similar!

Ask HN: When will Hotwire release Strada?
text:
I've been waiting to play around with Strada, from basecamp/hey for a couple of years now, but the release keeps getting pushed back.

On the site (https://hotwired.dev/) they explain that Strada will "Standardizes the way that web and native parts of a mobile hybrid application talk to each other via HTML bridge attributes. This makes it easy to progressively level-up web interactions with native replacements."

in 2021 it was supposed to be released later in 2021: https://web.archive.org/web/20211128183813/https://hotwired.dev/

in 2022 it was supposed to be released later in 2022: https://web.archive.org/web/20221104081346/https://hotwired.dev/

And now, it ids scheduled for 2023.

Anybody know when we should expect an official release?
